SIMPLE: wallflower
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wallflower
<hw>Wall"flow`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A perennial, cruciferous plant (<spn>Cheiranthus
Cheiri</spn>), with sweet-scented flowers varying in color from yellow
to orange and deep red. In Europe it very common on old walls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is sometimes extended to other species of
<gen>Cheiranthus</gen> and of the related genus <gen>Erysimum</gen>,
especially the American <stype>Western wallflower</stype> (<spn>Erysimum
asperum</spn>), a biennial herb with orange-yellow flowers.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lady at a ball, who, either from choice, or
because not asked to dance, remains a spectator.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>In Australia, the desert poison
bush (<spn>Gastrolobium grandiflorum</spn>); -- called also
<altname>native wallflower</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wallhick</ent>⟦br⟧
